# Git Workflow Conventions

## Commit Format (Conventional Commits)

```
type(scope): description

[optional body — explain WHY not WHAT]

[optional footer: Refs #123, Closes #456, BREAKING CHANGE: ...]
```

### Types

| Type | When to Use |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New feature or capability |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `docs` | Documentation only |
| `style` | Formatting, no logic change |
| `refactor` | Code restructuring, no behavior change |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `chore` | Build, CI, tooling changes |
| `ci` | CI/CD pipeline changes |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |

### Scopes (Exodus product scopes)

| Scope | Repo | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `core` | exodus-core | Shared kernel changes |
| `llm` | exodus-core | LLM router, model routing |
| `auth` | exodus-core | Auth and tenancy |
| `security` | exodus-core | PromptGuard, injection defense |
| `plan` | ironlayer_oss | Plan engine |
| `lineage` | ironlayer_oss | Column-level lineage |
| `cost` | ironlayer_oss | Cost modeling |
| `mcp` | ironlayer_oss | MCP server tools |
| `terraform` | ironlayer_infra, exodus-terraform | Infrastructure |
| `dbt` | ironlayer_infra | Data transformation |
| `extractors` | ironlayer_infra | Data ingestion |
| `agents` | exodus-autopilot | AI agent fleet |
| `github-app` | exodus-autopilot | Exodus Review Engine |
| `cicd` | exodus-autopilot | CI/CD engine |
| `billing` | exodus-autopilot | Stripe billing |
| `cli` | Any | CLI tool changes |
| `config` | Any | Configuration changes |
| `docs` | Any | Documentation |
| `ai` | iron-layer-dev-workspace | AI config, rules, skills |
| `standards` | iron-layer-dev-workspace | Coding standards |

### Examples

```
feat(plan): add column-level impact scoring to execution plan
feat(agents): two-pass PR review with local Ollama pass 1
fix(github-app): handle webhook timeout with ThreadPoolExecutor queuing
feat(terraform): add GitHub org repo provisioning with branch protection
docs(dbt): add YAML schema for all staging models
test(agents): add OutcomeStore confidence scoring unit tests
ci(github-app): add GitHub Actions self-hosted runner on Mac Studio
feat(mcp): add lineage query tool to MCP server
refactor(core): extract LLM router to standalone module
chore(ai): sync Cursor rules and Claude skills to exodus architecture
```

## Branch Naming

```
feature/<description>       # New features
fix/<issue-description>     # Bug fixes
docs/<topic>                # Documentation updates
refactor/<area>             # Code cleanup
ci/<pipeline>               # CI/CD changes
infra/<resource>            # Terraform/infrastructure
chore/<task>                # Maintenance tasks
```

Examples:
- `feature/two-pass-pr-review`
- `fix/ollama-fallback-timeout`
- `infra/github-org-repo-management`
- `ci/mac-studio-self-hosted-runner`

## PR Guidelines

1. Title follows conventional commit format
2. Description includes: **Summary**, **Test Plan**, **Checklist**
3. Link to UNIFIED_BACKLOG.md item (e.g., `Refs I-5-E2-S3`)
4. Human approval required before merge — never auto-merge
5. Autopilot Review Engine will post BLOCK/WARN/NOTE findings
6. Address all BLOCK findings before requesting human review
7. WARN findings: fix or document intentional deviation
